history.content:
The waitlist number is solely based on registration order, and does not reflect priority in getting off the waitlist.

You should assume that the enrollment numbers will be based on what the system currently displays. I am given to understand that 188, in particular, is done hiring TAs.

Just a general question: the general page for Getting into CS Courses says the following for Phase II:

In Phase II, all declared LSCS and EECS majors will be enrolled starting from the beginning of the existing waitlist. Any UC student can put themselves on the waitlist
If a CS upper div is filled with non-CS / EECS majors, is the position on a waitlist that a student holds including their priority (meaning if I am position 100, all 99 people ahead of me are CS declared / EECS)? Or is there a chance the student can move up based on their status
Also, I've noticed that 188 previous enrollment was 600 last Spring, and 16a was almost 800. Is it reasonable to assume these figures will be met for this upcoming fall?
history.subject: CS Enrollment for Phase II / Past section enrollment (188 and 16a)
